The paper deals with topics related to cryptography, information theory, and computational complexity, which are all covered by cs.CR. The paper also involves the construction of extractors and codes, which are fundamental objects in computer science and are studied in cs.IT and cs.DS. The paper also uses techniques from combinatorics, which is covered by cs.CC, and the study of randomness, which is covered by cs.CY.
